---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "Hong Kong eTAX Guide: How to File Taxes Online in 2025";
const description = "Hong Kong eTAX guide for filing taxes online. Learn how to register for eTAX, file your salaries tax return, check your assessment, and pay tax online.";
const image = "/images/blogs/hong-kong-etax-guide.svg";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} image={image}>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-canvas dark:bg-primary">
    <main class="min-h-screen">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="mb-6 text-sm">
          <ol class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2"><a href="/" class="text-link hover:underline dark:text-link">Home</a></li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-muted">/</span><a href="/blogs" class="text-link hover:underline dark:text-link">Blogs</a></li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-muted">/</span><span class="font-medium text-ink dark:text-on-primary" aria-current="page">Hong Kong eTAX Guide</span></li>
          </ol>
        </nav>

        <article class="prose max-w-none">
          <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-ink mb-4 dark:text-on-primary">Hong Kong eTAX Guide: How to File Taxes Online in 2025</h1>
          <p class="text-lg text-body dark:text-muted">Last updated: July 2026 | 10 min read</p>

          <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-body dark:text-muted">
            <p>The Inland Revenue Department's eTAX system is the fastest and most convenient way to manage your Hong Kong taxes online. From filing individual returns to viewing assessments, paying tax, and applying for holdover of provisional tax, eTAX streamlines every step of the tax process. This guide explains how to register for eTAX, file your salaries tax return, check your assessment, pay taxes, and resolve common eTAX issues. For a complete picture of filing requirements, read our <a href="/blogs/hong-kong-tax-deadline-calendar" class="text-link hover:underline dark:text-link">Hong Kong tax deadline calendar</a>.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">How to Register for eTAX</h2>
            <p>Registering for eTAX requires your personal details and identification. You can register online using your Hong Kong identity card number and other identifying information, or you may request an invitation code from the IRD by calling their customer service hotline. Once registered, you will receive a user account credentials email with instructions to activate your account. The IRD recommends using a strong, unique password and enabling two-factor authentication where available. After activation, you can log in using your eTAX account number and password to access all IRD services.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Filing Individual Tax Returns</h2>
            <p>Filing your individual tax return on eTAX is straightforward. After logging in, select the tax year and the type of return you wish to file. For most individuals, this is the Salaries Tax Return (BIR60). You can enter your employment income, MPF contributions, personal allowances, and allowable deductions directly in the eTAX interface. The system will automatically calculate your tax under both the progressive rate and standard rate, showing which is more favorable. You can save a draft return and return to it later before submission. Once submitted, you will receive an electronic confirmation.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Viewing Your Assessment</h2>
            <p>After submitting your tax return, you can view your assessment notice online through eTAX. The assessment notice shows your total assessable income, deductions, taxable income, tax payable under both rate systems, and any provisional tax due. Review the assessment carefully to ensure all allowances and deductions were correctly applied. If you notice an error, you can notify the IRD through eTAX or in writing. For complex corrections, you may need to provide additional supporting documents. Our <a href="/blogs/hong-kong-tax-allowances-deductions" class="text-link hover:underline dark:text-link">Hong Kong tax allowances and deductions guide</a> can help you verify your assessment calculations.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Paying Tax Online</h2>
            <p>eTAX supports multiple electronic payment options. You can pay using a credit card, PPS, or bank transfer through the IRD's secure payment portal. Payments made through eTAX are instantly reflected in your tax account. You can also authorize automatic payments or set up recurring payments for provisional tax installments. Always keep a record of your payment confirmation for future reference. If you are unsure about the amount due, check your assessment notice or use our <a href="/countries/hong-kong/salaries-tax/salaries-tax-calculator" class="text-link hover:underline dark:text-link">Hong Kong tax calculator</a> to estimate your liability before paying.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Holdover Applications</h2>
            <p>If you anticipate that your income will decrease in the coming year, you can apply for a holdover of provisional tax through eTAX. The application requires you to provide an estimate of your expected income for the next year and supporting evidence, such as a contract of employment or financial projection. The IRD will review your application and notify you of the outcome. A successful holdover reduces your immediate financial burden and aligns your payments with your actual tax liability. See our <a href="/blogs/hong-kong-provisional-tax-guide" class="text-link hover:underline dark:text-link">Hong Kong provisional tax guide</a> for more on when to apply.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Common eTAX Issues</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
              <li><strong>Account access problems:</strong> If you have forgotten your password, use the account recovery option. Contact the IRD if you encounter persistent login issues.</li>
              <li><strong>Failed submissions:</strong> Ensure all required fields are completed and all supporting documents are attached before submitting. Save drafts to avoid losing work.</li>
              <li><strong>Incorrect assessment:</strong> If eTAX displays an assessment you believe is wrong, submit an objection through the system or in writing within one month of the notice date.</li>
              <li><strong>Payment not reflected:</strong> Payments may take up to three business days to appear. If the delay persists, check your bank statement and contact the IRD with your payment reference number.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>For immediate assistance, visit <a href="https://www.ird.gov.hk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-link hover:underline dark:text-link">ird.gov.hk</a> or use the online enquiry form.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">What is eTAX?</h3>
            <p>eTAX is the Inland Revenue Department's electronic filing and tax management system. It allows taxpayers to file returns, view assessments, pay tax, and apply for holdover online.</p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">How do I log in to eTAX?</h3>
            <p>Log in using your eTAX account number and password. If you have not yet registered, visit <a href="https://www.ird.gov.hk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-link hover:underline dark:text-link">ird.gov.hk</a> and click the eTAX registration link to create an account.</p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Can I file my profits tax return online?</h3>
            <p>Yes, authorized signatories and tax representatives can file corporation profits tax returns through eTAX. See our <a href="/blogs/hong-kong-profits-tax-guide" class="text-link hover:underline dark:text-link">Hong Kong profits tax guide</a> for filing requirements.</p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">How long does it take for eTAX to process my payment?</h3>
            <p>Most online payments are reflected within three business days. Credit card and PPS payments are typically instant. If there is a delay, contact the IRD with your payment reference number.</p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Can I download my tax record from eTAX?</h3>
            <p>Yes, you can view and download your assessment notices, payment records, and return filings from the eTAX dashboard. Save or print these records for your personal files.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-12">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink mb-6 dark:text-on-primary">Related Calculators</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
              <a href="/countries/hong-kong/salaries-tax/salaries-tax-calculator" class="block rounded border p-4 hover:border-primary transition">HK Salaries Tax Calculator</a>
